\f0\b\fs62 \cf0 Orange Chipotle Chicken Thighs
\b0\fs52 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\i \cf0 Serves:  4 to 6 
\i0 \
		\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b\fs58 \cf0 Ingredients
\b0 \
  2       cans chipotle peppers in adobo sauce \
  3       cups orange marmalade \
  2      6 oz. cans tomato paste \
  2       cups orange juice \
  8       garlic cloves, peeled\
  1       bunch fresh cilantro \
  2/3   cup olive oil\
  2       tablespoon + 1 teaspoon kosher salt\
  2       teaspoon black pepper\
  12     chicken thighs\
  12     chicken drumsticks\
		\
		\
\ls1\ilvl0
\b Directions
\b0 \
In a food processor or blender, combine the chipotle peppers and adobo sauce, orange marmalade, tomato paste, orange juice, garlic, cilantro, olive oil, kosher salt, and black pepper. Puree until smooth. Pour marinade over chicken thighs and drums, and let marinate in a sealed bag or air-tight container at least 8 hours and up to 2 days.\
Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Arrange chicken thighs and drums in a large roasting pan, skin-side up.\'a0 (Pour in the marinade along with the chicken.) Bake about 45-55 minutes or until fully-cooked and the skin is fully caramelized and crispy (meat thermometer will read about 170 on the thickest part of the thighs).\'a0 Serve with sides of your choice and garnished with a bit of fresh cilantro.\
